  "text": "In this paper, we introduce a novel approach for efficient computation of space-varying convolution, based on the theory of matrix source coding; [CITATION_1] and we demonstrate how the technique can be used to efficiently implement the stray light reduction for digital cameras. The matrix source coding technique uses the method of lossy source coding which makes the dense matrix S sparse. This is done by first decorrelating the rows and columns of S and then quantizing the resulting compacted matrix so that most of its entries become zero. By making S sparse, we not only save storage, but we also dramatically reduce the computation of the required matrix-vector product.",
